HEADWORD: Tabarder
<hw>Tab"ard*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
wears a tabard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A scholar on the foundation of Queen's College,
Oxford, England, whose original dress was a tabard.</def>
<rj><au>Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

